abstract: Earnings met expectations, as AT&T’s wireless business continued to grow fast enough to make up for its shrinking traditional service.
snippet: Earnings met expectations, as AT&T’s wireless business continued to grow fast enough to make up for its shrinking traditional service.
lead_paragraph: Profit at AT&T, the telecommunications company, jumped 22 percent in the first quarter, meeting expectations, as its wireless business continued to grow fast enough to make up for its shrinking traditional service.

headline.print_headline: Wireless Unit Helps Lift AT&T’s Profit by 22%
